<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-01-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-01-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Sleeper</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-01-30"><hi rend="italic">January 30,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Sleeper reports compliance with the department’s telegram of 30th,
                            relative to the Seaboard Rice Milling Company, and adds that the answer
                            of foreign office will be made known to the department as soon as
                            possible.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>